 BLACKBODY THEORY. I KNEW THE PROBLEM WAS FUNDAMENTAL, AND I KNEW
 THE ANSWER. I HAD TO FIND A THEORETICAL EXPLANATION AT ANY COST,
 EXCEPT FOR THE INVIOLABLITY OF THE TWO LAWS OF THERMODYNAMICS.
   -- MAX PLANCK, 1931
